Azure Application Gateway is a web traffic load balancer that operates at the application layer (Layer 7).

Features include:

* URL-based routing
* SSL termination
* Web Application Firewall (WAF)

For example, traffic can be routed to different backend services based on URL paths.

A real-life use case is routing requests like /api to backend servers and /images to storage services.

Another example is protecting web applications from attacks using WAF.

Application Gateway enhances security and intelligent routing.
